bestBHT.bht: When the workers received their wages, they expressed their discontent by grumbling and complaining against the householder. The word murmur itself carries the connotation of a sound that suits the meaning, perhaps similar to the grumbling and complaining we are familiar with. It is important to note that this expression of dissatisfaction does not necessarily indicate a moral failing, but rather a response to the disparities in compensation. The workers were dissatisfied with the perceived unfairness of their reward, highlighting the external privileges of the Gospel dispensation and the inheritance reserved for the sanctified.

Jamieson-Fausset-Brown: 11. And when they had received it,
they murmured against the goodman of the house—rather, "the
householder," the word being the same as in :-.
Albert Barnes: The goodman of the house - The original...should have been so translated here.
Archibald T. Robertson: They murmured (εγογγυζον). Onomatopoetic word, the meaning suiting the sound.
Our words murmur and grumble are similar.
Probably here inchoative imperfect, began to grumble.
John Gill: The external privileges of the Gospel dispensation, an inheritance among them that are sanctified...
